.TH "tipc_aead_mem_alloc" 9 "tipc_aead_mem_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_aead_mem_alloc \- Allocate memory for AEAD request operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" tipc_aead_mem_alloc
.BI "(struct crypto_aead *tfm "  ","
.BI "unsigned int crypto_ctx_size "  ","
.BI "u8 **iv "  ","
.BI "struct aead_request **req "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist **sg "  ","
.BI "int nsg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tfm" 12
cipher handle to be registered with the request
.IP "crypto_ctx_size" 12
size of crypto context for callback
.IP "iv" 12
returned pointer to IV data
.IP "req" 12
returned pointer to AEAD request data
.IP "sg" 12
returned pointer to SG lists
.IP "nsg" 12
number of SG lists to be allocated
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate memory to store the crypto context data, AEAD request, IV and SG
lists, the memory layout is as follows:
crypto_ctx || iv || aead_req || sg[]
.SH "RETURN"
the pointer to the memory areas in case of success, otherwise NULL
